3
00:00:24,724 --> 00:00:26,190
[ Crunching Continues ]

4
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:28,126
[ Crunching Plays Back ]

5
00:00:28,128 --> 00:00:29,160
Gene.

6
00:00:29,162 --> 00:00:30,461
Gene.
[ Crunching Continues ]

7
00:00:30,463 --> 00:00:32,397
[ Sighs ]
Gene.
[ Burps ]

8
00:00:32,399 --> 00:00:33,531
What?
Stop.

9
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:35,333
Bob, no more
newspaper, please.

10
00:00:35,335 --> 00:00:37,769
My parents are gonna
be here any minute.
I know.

11
00:00:37,771 --> 00:00:39,137
You know how I know
they're coming?

12
00:00:39,139 --> 00:00:42,140
Because you go into a crazy
cleaning frenzy every time.

13
00:00:42,142 --> 00:00:45,343
It's like the way animals
freak out before an earthquake.

14
00:00:45,345 --> 00:00:47,412
That's nice.
That's not true!

15
00:00:47,414 --> 00:00:48,212
She's spooked.

16
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:49,814
Louise, you're getting
cereal everywhere.

17
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:52,283
[ Voice Quavering ]
I'm having a seizure!

18
00:00:52,285 --> 00:00:54,485
Put a wallet
in my mouth!

19
00:00:54,487 --> 00:00:55,119
It passed.

20
00:00:55,121 --> 00:00:57,221
Look at this place.
It's a disaster.

21
00:00:57,223 --> 00:00:58,656
You haven't even
fixed the leak yet.

22
00:00:58,658 --> 00:01:00,758
Come on.
Linda, the leak is contained.

23
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:01,893
[ Dripping ]
Bobby!

24
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:04,295
What?
You barely notice those.

25
00:01:04,297 --> 00:01:05,530
[ Yelps ]
I'm okay.

26
00:01:05,532 --> 00:01:09,434
Trust me, Bobby.
My mother will notice
that our ceiling is leaking.

27
00:01:09,436 --> 00:01:10,868
[ Sighs ]
Yeah, you're right.

28
00:01:10,870 --> 00:01:13,805
She will--
repeatedly and loudly.

29
00:01:13,807 --> 00:01:15,373
Just fix it, please.

30
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:17,708
Be my all-American
fix-it man, Bobby.

31
00:01:17,710 --> 00:01:19,844
Fine. I'll go up to the attic
and fix the leak.

32
00:01:19,846 --> 00:01:22,313
But I also need you
and the kids to work out...

33
00:01:22,315 --> 00:01:23,481
whose room my folks
are sleeping in,

34
00:01:23,483 --> 00:01:26,250
because I have to go
check the bathroom
for stray hairs.

35
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:28,286
No one sheds
like this family.

36
00:01:28,288 --> 00:01:29,620
It's like
a bunch of Chewbaccas.

37
00:01:29,622 --> 00:01:31,722
So where are Grandma
and Grandpa gonna sleep?

38
00:01:31,724 --> 00:01:34,592
Gene's room
smells like farts.
That makes sense.

39
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:35,893
Great. Well, we'll
put 'em in there then.

40
00:01:35,895 --> 00:01:39,197
Maybe they'll leave sooner
when they smell farts.
Yeah.

41
00:01:39,199 --> 00:01:40,498
Gene can sleep with me
in my room...

42
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,633
as long as he doesn't
mind my night terrors.
Huh?

43
00:01:42,635 --> 00:01:45,670
Remember you let me watch
Night of the Living Dead
when I was eight?

44
00:01:45,672 --> 00:01:48,840
So now I wake up every night
standing in the middle
of my room,

45
00:01:48,842 --> 00:01:50,374
scratching the air
and kicking.

46
00:01:50,376 --> 00:01:52,243
Oh, good.
Wait.
You still get those?

47
00:01:52,245 --> 00:01:53,478
Yeah.
They're weirder now.
Oh, boy.

48
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:57,915
I think my subconscious fears
and my budding sexuality
are getting all mixed up.

49
00:01:57,917 --> 00:01:59,450
Okay-- Tina, I don't
want to hear about this.

50
00:01:59,452 --> 00:02:02,720
So I think I'm being
attacked by zombies
and I start screaming,

51
00:02:02,722 --> 00:02:06,357
"Do you wanna make out?"
And I make out with it.

52
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:07,492
Hmm.

53
00:02:07,494 --> 00:02:09,660
I might just bunk
with Gram and Gramps.

54
00:02:09,662 --> 00:02:13,297
Okay, enough.
Gene, Louise,
you sleep in Tina's room.

55
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:15,900
Tina, you're quarantined.
You sleep alone.

56
00:02:15,902 --> 00:02:17,869
We'll strap you down
or something.

57
00:02:17,871 --> 00:02:19,904
Leave my lips free.

58
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:22,707
Hey. Hey!

59
00:02:22,709 --> 00:02:25,276
Gene, just 'cause Grandma
and Grandpa are coming...

60
00:02:25,278 --> 00:02:27,478
doesn't mean you're gonna
get out of doing homework.

61
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,680
How far are you
on that history report?

62
00:02:29,682 --> 00:02:31,282
So far I just got the title--

63
00:02:31,284 --> 00:02:34,418
"History: A Blast
From the Past."

64
00:02:34,420 --> 00:02:36,554
Okay. After we get
my parents settled,

65
00:02:36,556 --> 00:02:38,322
your father's gonna
help you with that.

66
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:40,658
- Right, Bob?
- Have it on my desk by 5:00.

67
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:43,794
I am not writing
your report for you.

68
00:02:43,796 --> 00:02:44,295
Hey.

69
00:02:44,297 --> 00:02:46,898
Okay, everybody, I have
an announcement to make.

70
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,300
I am on a ladder.
Stop shaking it.

71
00:02:49,302 --> 00:02:50,801
I feel like I shouldn't
have to say that.

72
00:02:50,803 --> 00:02:53,571
Dad, why do you get so mad
when Grandma Gloria...

73
00:02:53,573 --> 00:02:55,306
and Grandpa Al
come over to visit?

74
00:02:55,308 --> 00:02:58,509
Do you hate them?
I don't hate them.
Just Grandma.

75
00:02:58,511 --> 00:03:01,312
Or-- I don't hate her,
just the sound she makes.

76
00:03:01,314 --> 00:03:04,348
And her voice.
And the things she says.

77
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:05,616
Aye!

78
00:03:05,618 --> 00:03:07,552
Al!
[ Gasping ]

79
00:03:07,554 --> 00:03:09,554
[ Clears Throat ]
[ Groans ]

80
00:03:09,556 --> 00:03:10,421
[ Shutter Clicks ]

81
00:03:10,423 --> 00:03:12,890
Wanna hear
my impression of her?
Yes.

82
00:03:12,892 --> 00:03:13,724
[ As Grandma ]
Al!

83
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:15,560
[ Linda ]
I'm not hearing
this, right?

84
00:03:15,562 --> 00:03:19,330
Sorry. I mean,
she's your gram-gram.
We love her.

85
00:03:19,332 --> 00:03:21,332
[ Whispers ]
We hate her.

86
00:03:22,401 --> 00:03:23,267
I fixed the leak!

87
00:03:23,269 --> 00:03:24,936
[ Linda ] Good!
Don't stay up there
too long,

88
00:03:24,938 --> 00:03:29,607
'cause I want us all to
have a nice visit before
we open the restaurant!

89
00:03:29,609 --> 00:03:32,476
Uh, I mean, almost done!

90
00:03:33,445 --> 00:03:34,812
Huh?

91
00:03:34,814 --> 00:03:36,447
[ Groans ]

92
00:03:36,449 --> 00:03:37,481
Wow. This is amazing.

93
00:03:37,483 --> 00:03:39,417
Whose room am I behind?
[ Tina, Muffled ]
Mine.

94
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:42,987
- [ Muffled ] Hi, Tina.
- Are you in the wall
or in my horse poster?

95
00:03:42,989 --> 00:03:44,555
Please say "horse poster."

96
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:46,891
I'm a horse.
[ Imitates Whinnying ]

97
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:48,693
Oh, wait.
I can go sideways too.

98
00:03:48,695 --> 00:03:49,994
Are you
in another dimension?

99
00:03:49,996 --> 00:03:53,431
Do you see a lion or
a witch or a wardrobe?

100
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:53,764
A what?

101
00:03:53,766 --> 00:03:57,368
A lion, a witch or a wardrobe!

102
00:03:57,370 --> 00:03:59,971
- Why are you
saying that, Gene?
- It's a book.

103
00:03:59,973 --> 00:04:02,006
Oh, right, right.
A kids' book. Yeah.

104
00:04:02,008 --> 00:04:04,375
Yeah, by Salman Rushdie.
[ Scoffs ]

105
00:04:04,377 --> 00:04:06,777
It's not
by Salman Rushdie.
Of course it is.

106
00:04:06,779 --> 00:04:07,712
It isn't.
Yes, it is.

107
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:09,947
I'm not gonna talk
to you any more, Gene.
I'm in a wall.

108
00:04:09,949 --> 00:04:13,050
Go look it up though.
I just did.
It's Salman Rushdie.

109
00:04:13,052 --> 00:04:14,819
[ Doorbell Rings ]
[ Linda ]
They're here!

110
00:04:14,821 --> 00:04:18,456
[ Linda ] Bob, come out
of the wall, please!
Yeah.

111
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:20,024
Hello!

112
00:04:20,026 --> 00:04:20,958
[ Grunting ]
[ Grandma ]
Al!

113
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:24,061
Oh, my God.
Don't leave our bags
out there on the street!

114
00:04:24,063 --> 00:04:26,897
Are you crazy?
[ Clears Throat ]

115
00:04:26,899 --> 00:04:29,667
What are all these pots
doing on the floor?

116
00:04:29,669 --> 00:04:31,035
Bob will
pick 'em up, Mom.

117
00:04:31,037 --> 00:04:32,670
Bob, quit
fooling around in there.

118
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:35,873
You're gonna
get yourself stuck.

119
00:04:35,875 --> 00:04:39,977
Uh-- Uh, uh-oh!
Lin? Lin?

120
00:04:39,979 --> 00:04:40,945
Yes? What?

121
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:42,847
You're never
gonna believe this.

122
00:04:42,849 --> 00:04:44,649
What is it? What?

123
00:04:44,651 --> 00:04:46,384
I'm stuck!

124
00:04:47,586 --> 00:04:50,021
[ Sniffs ]
Shouldn't have farted.

125
00:04:52,491 --> 00:04:54,492
[ Grandma ]
Who's trapped in the wall?

126
00:04:54,494 --> 00:04:55,593
Bob.
[ Bob ]
Me.

127
00:04:55,595 --> 00:04:58,863
Bob can't fit in the wall.
He's overweight!

128
00:04:58,865 --> 00:05:00,831
Mom!
What?
He can't hear me.

129
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:03,100
[ Bob ]
Yes, I can.
I'm right here.

130
00:05:03,102 --> 00:05:04,669
Uh, I'd like to
order a hamburger.

131
00:05:04,671 --> 00:05:09,807
No, Al!
He can't have a hamburger.
He can have a turkey burger.

132
00:05:09,809 --> 00:05:12,643
There's no such thing
as a turkey burger.

133
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:14,979
Go read your Maxim.
Dad gets Maxim?

134
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:18,449
No. He found it
in the recycling
at the condo.

135
00:05:18,451 --> 00:05:19,884
Who's on the cover?

136
00:05:19,886 --> 00:05:21,519
The girls of Coyote Ugly.

137
00:05:21,521 --> 00:05:23,654
I don't think they're
even alive anymore.

138
00:05:23,656 --> 00:05:25,690
Lin, we need to open
the restaurant.

139
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:26,991
Hey, I bet
I can get down there.

140
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:29,493
What are you talking about?
You can go down?

141
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:31,629
[ Bob ]
Kids, you meet me
down there, okay?

142
00:05:31,631 --> 00:05:33,030
You're gonna be
my eyes and my hands.

143
00:05:33,032 --> 00:05:36,600
Okay. We're down there.
No, you're not.
You haven't moved.

144
00:05:36,602 --> 00:05:38,936
I'm turning on the grill!
Beep, boop. Whoosh!

145
00:05:38,938 --> 00:05:42,673
That's not the sound
the grill makes.
Go down to the restaurant.

146
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:45,776
Okay, so the special
comes with feta cheese,

147
00:05:45,778 --> 00:05:47,712
and it's called
"Never Been Feta."

148
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:50,981
[ Chuckles ]
Did you hear that?
Are you laughing?

149
00:05:50,983 --> 00:05:51,782
[ Laughing ]

150
00:05:51,784 --> 00:05:54,452
I hear you laughing.
Are you writing it?

151
00:05:54,454 --> 00:05:57,822
Yep. "Never Been Feta."

152
00:05:57,824 --> 00:05:59,457
Good. All right,
I'm gonna go...

153
00:05:59,459 --> 00:06:00,958
get Tina set up
on the grill.

154
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,626
This is going great!

155
00:06:05,497 --> 00:06:07,131
[ Grunting ]

156
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:09,066
Hey, kids. Gene.
Louise.

157
00:06:09,068 --> 00:06:11,102
Hey!
Hey. Take this.

158
00:06:11,104 --> 00:06:12,837
That's my pee.
Oh.

159
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:13,671
Yeah.
[ Groans ]

160
00:06:13,673 --> 00:06:16,507
Empty it out
and bring it back, okay?
This will be our system.

161
00:06:16,509 --> 00:06:18,075
Uh--
You're my pee guy.

162
00:06:18,077 --> 00:06:19,443
Dad's pee.
[ Groans ]

163
00:06:19,445 --> 00:06:22,012
Bob, I called Teddy
the contractor.

164
00:06:22,014 --> 00:06:23,981
He's coming right away
to get you out.

165
00:06:23,983 --> 00:06:26,751
What? No.
Lin, that's not necessary.

166
00:06:26,753 --> 00:06:28,919
Of course it is.
You're stuck in the wall.

167
00:06:28,921 --> 00:06:31,655
No, I know. Just--
You know how Teddy is.

168
00:06:31,657 --> 00:06:33,557
Talky Teddy.
Yap, yap, yap.

169
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:35,793
What, you don't have time
for his stories?

170
00:06:35,795 --> 00:06:37,995
Are you very, very
busy today?

171
00:06:37,997 --> 00:06:39,797
Uh, no.

172
00:06:39,799 --> 00:06:41,732
You're in a tight spot,
huh, Bobby?

173
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:42,600
A little bit, Teddy.
Gee.

174
00:06:42,602 --> 00:06:45,069
I've heard of buildings
like this, you know,
with false walls.

175
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,537
- Uh-huh.
- It's a prohibition thing.

176
00:06:46,539 --> 00:06:49,006
Oh.
Yeah, this town, it used
to be a bootleggers' port.

177
00:06:49,008 --> 00:06:50,541
A lot of people
don't know that.

178
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:51,242
That's interesting.
Yeah.

179
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,978
My great uncle used to run
a speakeasy here in town.
Uh-huh.

180
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:55,846
It was called Swanky's.
Place was called Swanky's.

181
00:06:55,848 --> 00:06:58,182
You ever hear of a cocktail
called the Swanky Panky?
No.

182
00:06:58,184 --> 00:07:02,186
It's made with
two parts vermouth--
Teddy, Teddy, Teddy. Listen.

183
00:07:02,188 --> 00:07:04,054
Don't get me out
today, okay?

184
00:07:04,056 --> 00:07:05,689
Tell Linda you have
to come back tomorrow.

185
00:07:05,691 --> 00:07:08,926
I got the Sawzall
in the truck. I don't even--
No, no. Teddy, listen.

186
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:11,695
Tell her that you need
a permit or something.

187
00:07:11,697 --> 00:07:13,764
You want to stay
in the wall, Bob?

188
00:07:13,766 --> 00:07:15,132
Don't judge, Teddy.
Don't judge.

189
00:07:15,134 --> 00:07:18,536
There's nothing wrong
with a man enjoying
his crawl space...

190
00:07:18,538 --> 00:07:19,270
till his in-laws leave.

191
00:07:19,272 --> 00:07:21,639
No, it's just, you know,
I heard about this guy...

192
00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:24,041
that hid out in a wall
from the police.

193
00:07:24,043 --> 00:07:25,209
He went bonkers, Bob.
Yeah.

194
00:07:25,211 --> 00:07:28,112
When they found him, he was
chewing on a two-by-four--
Mm-hmm.

195
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:31,148
wearing nothing
but copper wire.
That's a great story, Teddy.

196
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:32,249
Just come back tomorrow.

197
00:07:32,251 --> 00:07:35,186
Okay. I still gotta
charge you for today though.

198
00:07:35,188 --> 00:07:36,687
Today? You just
stood there, talking.

199
00:07:36,689 --> 00:07:41,091
Bob, you know, my therapist says
that if I don't value my time,
nobody's going to.

200
00:07:41,093 --> 00:07:42,092
All right.
You're right. Right.

201
00:07:42,094 --> 00:07:43,761
All right.
I'm just gonna write it up...

202
00:07:43,763 --> 00:07:45,696
as a consultation though--
friend prices.

203
00:07:45,698 --> 00:07:46,597
Do whatever you have to do,

204
00:07:46,599 --> 00:07:49,233
and just drop the bill
down the shaft.
All right.

205
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:51,635
[ Teddy ]
Did you get it?
[ Bob ] Did you drop it?

206
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:52,670
[ Teddy ]
I dropped it.
I didn't get it.

207
00:07:52,672 --> 00:07:55,606
[ Teddy ] Well, I can't have
the-- you know,
the things outstanding.

208
00:07:55,608 --> 00:07:57,575
Teddy, I'll look for it,
all right?
Find it.

209
00:07:57,577 --> 00:08:02,713
[ Bob ] Write another one then!
I don't have--
Now I gotta go to the truck.

210
00:08:02,715 --> 00:08:03,848
Okay. As you can see,

211
00:08:03,850 --> 00:08:07,751
I'm spending my first night
inside the walls
of my own house.

212
00:08:07,753 --> 00:08:11,088
I borrowed Gene's camera
so I can document my experience.

213
00:08:11,090 --> 00:08:12,756
[ Linda ]
Come on, Bob.
It's late.

214
00:08:12,758 --> 00:08:15,359
And Louise has loaned me
her Kuchi Kupi night light.

215
00:08:15,361 --> 00:08:18,863
[ Louise ] Kuchi Kopi.
Kuchi Kopi.
Kuchi Kopi night light.

216
00:08:18,865 --> 00:08:22,900
Anyway, here's where
I'm gonna sleep tonight.
I'll show you.

217
00:08:22,902 --> 00:08:25,636
[ Grandma ]
Oh! Al! Yes!

218
00:08:25,638 --> 00:08:27,805
[ Grandma Moaning ]

219
00:08:27,807 --> 00:08:28,672
Oh, my God.

220
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:32,109
Oh, my God. I think
Linda's parents are having sex.

221
00:08:32,111 --> 00:08:34,745
[ Moaning Continues ]

222
00:08:34,747 --> 00:08:39,817
I hope they're using protection,
'cause I am not
taking care of that baby.

223
00:08:39,819 --> 00:08:41,085
I'm gonna sample it.

224
00:08:41,087 --> 00:08:44,555
[ Grandma Continues
Moaning ]

225
00:08:44,557 --> 00:08:46,924
[ Moaning ]

226
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:51,862
Well, hello.
Funny seeing you here.

227
00:08:52,264 --> 00:08:54,632
Whoa.
Double trouble.

228
00:08:54,634 --> 00:08:56,901
Okay, let's do this.

229
00:08:56,903 --> 00:08:58,369
[ Groaning ]

230
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:01,739
- You sound like my grandmother.
- What? I can't hear you.

231
00:09:01,741 --> 00:09:04,308
And you sound
