468
00:18:53,732 --> 00:18:54,865
I found him.

469
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:56,733
[ Yelps ]
Ow! That's hot!

470
00:18:56,735 --> 00:18:58,635
[ Grandma Exclaims ]
[ Bob Coughs ]

471
00:18:58,637 --> 00:19:00,470
[ Bob Moans ]
[ Grandma Moans ]

472
00:19:00,472 --> 00:19:01,771
[ Bob ]
Ow!
[ Moans ]

473
00:19:01,773 --> 00:19:03,707
[ Grandma ]
Ow!
[ Moans ]

474
00:19:05,276 --> 00:19:07,844
[ Toilet Flushes ]
[ Groans ]
Wow.

475
00:19:07,846 --> 00:19:08,945
Much better.

476
00:19:08,947 --> 00:19:11,214
Bad modeling,
poor boundaries--

477
00:19:11,216 --> 00:19:13,617
Well, really,
no boundaries.
[ Chuckles ]

478
00:19:13,619 --> 00:19:14,885
I'm gonna have
to make some calls.

479
00:19:14,887 --> 00:19:17,354
Wait. Mr. Frond,
now that I have
a clear head,

480
00:19:17,356 --> 00:19:19,623
I want to apologize--
to everybody.

481
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:21,558
Hiding in the walls
was selfish and dumb.

482
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:24,361
And, Linda,
I'm sorry I called you
Nagatha Christie.

483
00:19:24,363 --> 00:19:27,531
It was in the heat
of the moment,
and it was really dumb.

484
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:29,533
Aw. Thank you, Bobby.

485
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:31,368
I meant I can do better.

486
00:19:31,370 --> 00:19:33,904
Like Spiro Nagnew.
[ Chuckles ]

487
00:19:33,906 --> 00:19:35,539
All right.
Quit while you're ahead.

488
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:38,675
Naggedy Ann?
Secretary of Nagriculture?

489
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:40,377
Ha!
Now that one's funny.

490
00:19:40,379 --> 00:19:41,912
That one's funny.
I like--
[ Chuckles ]

491
00:19:41,914 --> 00:19:45,415
I'm not a-- I'm not a nag.
It's funny though.
I like it.

492
00:19:45,417 --> 00:19:48,518
Social Services?
Now hold on there, pal.

493
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,387
Hey--
Are you married?

494
00:19:50,389 --> 00:19:52,522
You have kids?
No, and no.

495
00:19:52,524 --> 00:19:56,726
Listen to me.
My daughter is the best
mother in the world,

496
00:19:56,728 --> 00:20:01,231
and this one--
he is nuts,
but guess what.

497
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:03,767
Having a family
makes you go nuts.

498
00:20:03,769 --> 00:20:05,268
So if you don't
have kids,

499
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:08,438
I don't think
you know enough to be
calling in anyone.

500
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:12,008
In fact, I don't think you
come out looking so good
here yourself.

501
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:17,714
I wonder if you even got
permission from the school
to come over here today.

502
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:19,950
- He didn't.
- He took us away from learning!

503
00:20:19,952 --> 00:20:24,854
We were in the car with
Mr. Frond, and he didn't
make us wear seat belts.

504
00:20:24,856 --> 00:20:26,456
What?
[ Stammering ]

505
00:20:26,458 --> 00:20:31,661
How about you put your phone
and your little notebook back
in your pocket there...

506
00:20:31,663 --> 00:20:33,797
and leave this
family alone!

507
00:20:33,799 --> 00:20:37,334
[ Gasps ]
Okay. All right.
All right.

508
00:20:37,336 --> 00:20:39,836
[ Chuckling ]
All right.
All right.

509
00:20:39,838 --> 00:20:42,639
Gloria, thank you.

510
00:20:43,541 --> 00:20:45,275
Come back soon, you two.

511
00:20:45,277 --> 00:20:46,910
Bye, Gram.
Bye, Gramps.

512
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:49,446
See you in my dreams.

513
00:20:49,448 --> 00:20:51,615
Well, I have a room
to re-fart.

514
00:20:51,617 --> 00:20:54,618
Dad, can I have
my night light back now?
No.

515
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:55,885
Give it to me.
Stop it.

516
00:20:55,887 --> 00:20:57,087
Give it to me.
Stop it.

517
00:20:57,089 --> 00:20:57,954
Give it!
Stop it!

518
00:20:57,956 --> 00:20:59,489
It's my night light.
Don't-- Stop.

519
00:20:59,491 --> 00:21:00,991
This is embarrassing to me!
No!

520
00:21:00,993 --> 00:21:04,027
You're a grown man!
I'm keeping it!

